Members of the South African public are urged to wear a white ribbon as a symbolic pledge towards eliminating the scourge of woman and child abuse.  This year’s 16 Days of ­Activism of No Violence against Women and Children is observed from Saturday (25/11) until 10 December.  A sexual offences court will be launched during the campaign and it is hoped that it will ensure better access to the justice system.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  